          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The inelastic cross section of relativistic",
                "protons in Pb was determined indirectly by measuring",
                "the neutron distribution along a Lead spallation",
                "neutron source.",
                "The spallation neutron source was irradiated by 1, 1.5",
                "and 2 GeV protons. The experimental results were",
                "obtained using passive methods. By the use of the beam",
                "attenuation coefficient, deduced by a fitting procedure",
                "of experimental data, the inelastic cross section of",
                "protons in Pb was determined."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cylindrical Pb target, with 40 cm length and 8 cm in",
                "diameter covered with a paraffin moderator 6 cm in",
                "thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron distribution was studied on the",
                "paraffin moderator a long the target by using Solid",
                "State Nuclear Track Detectors(SSNTDs).",
                "Natural Cd foils (mass approx.2 gram, purity 99.9%,",
                "thickness 1 mm) were also used as an activation",
                "detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By author*.Each part of the neutron spectrum was",
                "measured by using two different techniques.",
                "Neutron fluencies are presented for three neutron",
                "energy ranges. Thermal neutrons with En < 1 eV, slow",
                " (1 eV < En < 10 keV) and fast neutrons",
                " (0.3 MeV < En < 3 MeV) are shown for an irradiation of",
                "the target with protons of 1 GeV. Slow neutrons were",
                "measured by Cd-nat activation method while thermal",
                "neutrons with En < 1 eV and fast neutrons by SSNTDs",
                "technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
